The paper deals with dimensionality reduction, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of the Johnson-Lindenstrauss lemma suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The focus on preserving distances within a set and to the rest of space suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of analysis to derive a tighter bound suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
